column5: Shot this video last time up at Jiggy...  http://ontariofishingreels.com/hammerhead/hammer2.html
Wow. First mistyriver1's giant Muskie, and now Moniques Pike. The stars must be lined up just right!!!
Great vid Bossman!!!  She was taking a heavy risk landing that one without a net!... those things will shake a hook into your hand in an instant!!!  I'm glad nobody was hurt!
Sweet! The fish is kinda scrawny though.  JF
TJ your such a tease I really thought she caught something fatter than the last critter.
Those little suckers combined with some trebles scare me more than the big ones.
TJ knows all about the little guys and trebles..eh TJ??   Nice pike Monique!
Great video TJ and way to go Monique  Thanks for sharing Leechman

To think I was going to claim that I taught Monique every think she knows about Fishin..... A what the hay I am still proud of my favorite student. I see if I can get you to catch  a little bigger Pike  next year at Lak Air.   Art
nice vid again TJ I just love how real the sound effects are the birds in the background sound like they were there wit hya.

the video was great, but I trumped Monique Saturday.  Caught a pike only 7 inches long, felt a bite, set the hook, nothing. Decided to check for weeds possibly, and the nightcrawler situation, still anything left on the harness? ,.....................ummmmmmmmmmmmmm, yah, gots a fish, dragging it on the worm harness. Good thing I checked as I did not feel anything unusual trolling, I would probably have drowned that poor little pike, it was the same size as the worm harness,
Whatever happend to "You can't go fishing without the net"?  Just yankin, nice vid.  Thanks for sharing it with us TJ.
